author: @raymondphilip6232
text: if you are having an error on pip installation. please follow my instruction subsequently:  1. In "Search"  type "Control Panel"  2. click "Programs"  3. click "Programs and Features"  4. search for whatever version of python you are using.  EXAMPLE : "Python 3.7.1 (64-bit)"  5. right click  6. pick "Change"  7. pick "Modify"  8. make sure every box is ticked   9. click next  10. make sure every box is ticked again  11. copy your "Customize install location"  EXAMPLE: "C:\Users\User\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python37\"  12. click "Install"  13. wait for it to complete downloading  14. In "Search" type "cmd"  15. type "cd (and then copy paste)"  16. delete "C:\Users\User\"  17. change all label from "\" into "/"  18. type "pip install Django"

text: when you hit the django-admin not recognized error do this.  To permanently set PATH:  Right click My computer in the desktop. Click Advanced System Settings on the left. Restart cmd.exe. (PATH will not change for already launched cmd.exe)

author: @saschabeh9505
text: The 404 is happening because the browser is not only asking for the URL that was typed in but also for a favicon file. Hence it sends a GET request for  the location of /favicon.ico which the server answers with an error code of 404, i.e. it has not found a resource at this location. The browser does not send this request again in subsequent page requests, so that is why you only see it when you send the first request.
